===Verb===
{{en-verb|echo|es}}

# {{context|of a sound or sound waves|intransitive|lang=en}} To reflect off of a surface and return.
# {{context|by extension|transitive|lang=en}} To repeat back precisely what another has just said: to copy in the imitation of a natural echo.
#* {{w|John Dryden}}
#*: Those peals are '''echoed''' by the Trojan throng.
#* Keble
#*: The wondrous sound / Is '''echoed''' on forever.
# {{context|by extension|transitive|lang=en}} To repeat (another's speech, opinion{{,}} etc.).
#* {{quote-magazine|year=2013|month=July-August|author=[http://www.americanscientist.org/authors/detail/sarah-glaz Sarah Glaz]
